entering a period

342
00:22:06,041 --> 00:22:07,834
of firestorm activity.

343
00:22:07,834 --> 00:22:10,875
Bersallin firestorms happen
on a seven-year cycle.

344
00:22:10,875 --> 00:22:13,291
They're not expecting any
for another eight months.

345
00:22:13,291 --> 00:22:14,667
We don't rendezvous
with the<i> Havana</i>

346
00:22:14,667 --> 00:22:16,000
for another two days.

347
00:22:16,000 --> 00:22:17,250
That would give us
plenty of opportunity

348
00:22:17,250 --> 00:22:18,583
to study this
phenomenon.

349
00:22:18,583 --> 00:22:20,458
Helm, set a course
for Bersallis III,

350
00:22:20,458 --> 00:22:22,125
warp five.
Aye, sir.

351
00:22:22,125 --> 00:22:25,041
Counselor, could I speak
with you in my ready room?

352
00:22:25,041 --> 00:22:26,959
You have the bridge,
Number One.

353
00:22:30,750 --> 00:22:32,875
Sit down, Counselor.

354
00:22:32,875 --> 00:22:36,750
I wanted to talk to you
about a matter of protocol.

355
00:22:39,291 --> 00:22:41,375
I know there are
no Starfleet regulations

356
00:22:41,375 --> 00:22:42,834
about a captain
becoming involved

357
00:22:42,834 --> 00:22:45,625
with a fellow officer.

358
00:22:45,625 --> 00:22:47,458
But--
You would like my opinion

359
00:22:47,458 --> 00:22:49,417
about you and
Commander Daren?

360
00:22:52,667 --> 00:22:54,542
It's that obvious?

361
00:22:54,542 --> 00:22:55,959
In a way
that pleases people

362
00:22:55,959 --> 00:22:58,542
who care about your happiness,
yes, it is.

363
00:22:58,542 --> 00:22:59,709
But I have to
be concerned

364
00:22:59,709 --> 00:23:01,875
about more
than my own happiness.

365
00:23:01,875 --> 00:23:04,417
And you think that
your feelings toward Nella

366
00:23:04,417 --> 00:23:06,959
could change the way
you function as captain?

367
00:23:06,959 --> 00:23:08,166
Yes.

368
00:23:08,166 --> 00:23:09,709
Relationships
with coworkers

369
00:23:09,709 --> 00:23:11,875
can be fraught
with consequences.

370
00:23:11,875 --> 00:23:13,542
That's true,

371
00:23:13,542 --> 00:23:15,333
but cutting yourself off
from your feelings

372
00:23:15,333 --> 00:23:16,500
can carry consequences

373
00:23:16,500 --> 00:23:18,542
that are just
as serious.

374
00:23:22,208 --> 00:23:25,041
You see, I've
always believed

375
00:23:25,041 --> 00:23:27,417
that becoming involved with
someone under my command

376
00:23:27,417 --> 00:23:29,667
would compromise
my objectivity.

377
00:23:31,417 --> 00:23:33,792
And yet...

378
00:23:33,792 --> 00:23:36,417
Captain, are you asking
my permission?

379
00:23:36,417 --> 00:23:38,333
If I were,
would you give it?

380
00:23:40,792 --> 00:23:42,750
Yes.

381
00:23:43,625 --> 00:23:44,917
(<i> door chimes</i> )

382
00:23:44,917 --> 00:23:46,625
Come in.

383
00:23:50,208 --> 00:23:51,917
Nella?

384
00:23:53,291 --> 00:23:55,458
Can I help you,
sir?

385
00:24:01,542 --> 00:24:03,125
(<i> sighs</i> )

386
00:24:03,125 --> 00:24:04,458
I'm really very sorry

387
00:24:04,458 --> 00:24:06,375
about what happened
in the turbolift.

388
00:24:06,375 --> 00:24:08,417
When the crew member
walked in,

389
00:24:08,417 --> 00:24:10,333
I felt very
self-conscious.

390
00:24:10,333 --> 00:24:11,583
It's going to take
a while

391
00:24:11,583 --> 00:24:13,000
for me to get used
to the idea

392
00:24:13,000 --> 00:24:15,709
of crew seeing
the two of us together.

393
00:24:17,041 --> 00:24:19,125
I understand.

394
00:24:19,125 --> 00:24:20,792
Now, I'm glad you told me.
For a minute there,

395
00:24:20,792 --> 00:24:22,834
I thought
I'd misread you.

396
00:24:22,834 --> 00:24:25,750
One kiss, and you're off
to find somebody else.

397
00:24:29,625 --> 00:24:33,041
I can assure you that I'm not
given to casual relationships.

398
00:24:36,458 --> 00:24:39,291
There is something
that I want to tell you...

399
00:24:41,291 --> 00:24:43,291
but not here.

400
00:24:43,291 --> 00:24:46,166
Do you remember
the folk melody that
I played to you this morning?

401
00:24:46,166 --> 00:24:48,625
Yes. Yeah.

402
00:24:48,625 --> 00:24:51,792
I learned it on a planet
called Kataan.

403
00:24:51,792 --> 00:24:53,417
Never heard of it.

404
00:24:53,417 --> 00:24:55,625
No, I'm not surprised.

405
00:24:55,625 --> 00:25:00,083
Its sun went nova more than
a thousand years ago.

406
00:25:00,083 --> 00:25:02,542
I don't understand.

407
00:25:04,792 --> 00:25:06,917
The<i> Enterprise</i> 
encountered a probe

408
00:25:06,917 --> 00:25:09,291
that had been sent
from the planet

409
00:25:09,291 --> 00:25:11,083
before it was destroyed.

410
00:25:11,083 --> 00:25:14,250
And it scanned me,
and I lost consciousness.

411
00:25:14,250 --> 00:25:18,041
And...

412
00:25:18,041 --> 00:25:22,083
in the space
of 25 minutes,

413
00:25:22,083 --> 00:25:26,875
I lived a lifetime
on that planet.

414
00:25:28,583 --> 00:25:30,583
I had a wife and...

415
00:25:30,583 --> 00:25:34,083
and children
and a grandchild.

416
00:25:35,709 --> 00:25:39,625
And it was
absolutely real to me.

417
00:25:39,625 --> 00:25:42,250
And when I awoke,

418
00:25:42,250 --> 00:25:46,458
all that I had left
of that life

419
00:25:46,458 --> 00:25:49,959
was the flute that
I'd taught myself to play.

420
00:25:51,083 --> 00:25:53,500
Why are you
telling me this?

421
00:25:53,500 --> 00:25:55,792
Because I want you
to understand

422
00:25:55,792 --> 00:25:58,125
what my music
means to me...

423
00:25:58,125 --> 00:26:00,291
(<i> sighs</i> )

424
00:26:02,208 --> 00:26:04,333
...and what it
means for me

425
00:26:04,333 --> 00:26:06,959
to be able to
share it with someone.

426
00:26:13,375 --> 00:26:15,333
Thank you.

427
00:26:32,417 --> 00:26:34,583
Hello.
Sir.

428
00:26:35,834 --> 00:26:38,125
Commander, I was
hoping to talk to you

429
00:26:38,125 --> 00:26:39,792
about Ensign Cabot's
transfer.

430
00:26:39,792 --> 00:26:41,834
Quantum mechanics doesn't
want to give him up.

431
00:26:41,834 --> 00:26:44,875
But he wants to come
to my department.

432
00:26:44,875 --> 00:26:48,375
How do you know that?
I offered it to him.

433
00:26:48,375 --> 00:26:50,041
Transfers are to
be approved by me

434
00:26:50,041 --> 00:26:51,625
before any offers
are made.

435
00:26:51,625 --> 00:26:52,667
I'm sorry.

436
00:26:52,667 --> 00:26:54,208
We were just talking,
and...

437
00:26:54,208 --> 00:26:56,959
It's all right, but Cabot
should stay where he is.

438
00:26:56,959 --> 00:26:59,750
Commander, please don't make
that decision final.

439
00:26:59,750 --> 00:27:01,834
I realize I shouldn't
have made the offer,

440
00:27:01,834 --> 00:27:03,792
but he's perfect
for the job,

441
00:27:03,792 --> 00:27:06,291
and quantum mechanics
is overstaffed, anyway.

442
00:27:06,291 --> 00:27:09,417
Commander, do you realize the
position you're putting me in?

443
00:27:09,417 --> 00:27:11,625
Well, I-I think
I'm just doing

444
00:27:11,625 --> 00:27:13,542
what any good
department head would do--

445
00:27:13,542 --> 00:27:16,166
trying to build
the best staff I can.

446
00:27:16,166 --> 00:27:18,750
Look, I'll review
the situation.

447
00:27:18,750 --> 00:27:20,500
I'll let you know
as soon as I can.

448
00:27:26,458 --> 00:27:29,625
(<i> door chimes</i> )
Come.

449
00:27:31,000 --> 00:27:32,750
May I have a minute?

450
00:27:32,750 --> 00:27:35,375
Yes, of course.
Come in, Number One.

451
00:27:35,375 --> 00:27:37,625
It's about Lieutenant
Commander Daren.

452
00:27:37,625 --> 00:27:39,542
As a department head,
she comes to me

453
00:27:39,542 --> 00:27:42,333
for systems allocation,
personnel transfers,

454
00:27:42,333 --> 00:27:43,917
things like that.

455
00:27:43,917 --> 00:27:46,208
Well...
I'm beginning to feel

456
00:27:46,208 --> 00:27:48,291
uncomfortable
with her requests.

457
00:27:51,417 --> 00:27:54,333
Because of her
relationship with me?

458
00:27:54,333 --> 00:27:56,291
Yes, sir.

459
00:28:04,375 --> 00:28:07,542
Are her requests unusual?
No.

460
00:28:07,542 --> 00:28:10,291
Would you say that she's
just trying to do her job?

461
00:28:10,291 --> 00:28:12,000
Yes, sir.

462
00:28:12,000 --> 00:28:15,208
Then let her do it, and you
feel free to do yours.

463
00:28:15,208 --> 00:28:18,250
Ship's resources are
your responsibility.

464
00:28:18,250 --> 00:28:22,125
I have always had absolute
confidence in your judgment.

465
00:28:22,125 --> 00:28:24,709
Thank you, sir.

466
00:28:29,458 --> 00:28:31,917
(<i> sighs</i> )

467
00:28:36,250 --> 00:28:38,625
I can't believe I'm going
to get the chance to study

468
00:28:38,625 --> 00:28:40,709
the firestorms
on Bersallis.

469
00:28:40,709 --> 00:28:42,250
Apparently,
they're generated

470
00:28:42,250 --> 00:28:44,458
by particle emissions
from the Bersallin sun.

471
00:28:44,458 --> 00:28:47,500
They cause a cascade effect
in the planet's atmosphere

472
00:28:47,500 --> 00:28:48,959
that...

473
00:28:48,959 --> 00:28:50,834
Oh, I'm boring you.

474
00:28:50,834 --> 00:28:53,208
No. No. No, you're not.

475
00:28:53,208 --> 00:28:54,458
Not at all.

476
00:28:54,458 --> 00:28:57,041
(<i> sighs</i> )

477
00:28:57,041 --> 00:28:59,041
It's just that...

478
00:28:59,041 --> 00:29:02,208
Commander Riker
came to see me this afternoon...

479
00:29:02,208 --> 00:29:03,542
about you.

480
00:29:04,750 --> 00:29:07,709
About the personnel
transfer.

481
00:29:07,709 --> 00:29:10,667
I<i> thought</i> 
he looked uncomfortable.

482
00:29:10,667 --> 00:29:13,333
He thought I was asking
for special treatment.

483
00:29:16,250 --> 00:29:19,083
I was just doing what I thought
was best for my department.

484
00:29:19,083 --> 00:29:21,000
And that's what I told him.

485
00:29:21,000 --> 00:29:24,625
But...
we have to be careful.

486
00:29:24,625 --> 00:29:27,750
Obviously, it's easy
for people to misunderstand.

487
00:29:27,750 --> 00:29:29,166
I don't like the thought

488
00:29:29,166 --> 00:29:32,333
of having to second-guess
people all the time.

489
00:29:32,333 --> 00:29:34,959
If I have to worry about what
people are thinking about me,

490
00:29:34,959 --> 00:29:37,083
I'll be concentrating
on the wrong thing

491
00:29:37,083 --> 00:29:38,709
and I won't be
as effective an officer.

492
00:29:38,709 --> 00:29:40,583
All I'm saying is

493
00:29:40,583 --> 00:29:42,458
that it's something
we have to be aware of,

494
00:29:42,458 --> 00:29:44,709
but you mustn't
compromise yourself.

495
00:29:44,709 --> 00:29:46,834
You must do
what you have to do,

496
00:29:46,834 --> 00:29:49,959
because if I find that
my head of stellar sciences

497
00:29:49,959 --> 00:29:53,417
isn't being effective,
then<i> I</i> shall do what<i> I</i> must do--

498
00:29:54,583 --> 00:29:56,333
and I shall replace her.

499
00:29:56,333 --> 00:29:58,875
Noted, sir.

500
00:29:58,875 --> 00:30:00,583
Now, I think that we should
just forget about this

501
00:30:00,583 --> 00:30:02,000
and enjoy our evening.

502
00:30:02,000 --> 00:30:05,875
What about that special
dessert you promised me?

503
00:30:05,875 --> 00:30:09,500
Right. Now, this is something
that I first tasted

504
00:30:09,500 --> 00:30:10,709
on Thelka IV...

